description.0: Elektra's off to Japan! While there, the assassin meets two of Wolverine's oldest friends, Yukio and young Amiko. Featuring the Silver Samurai!
description.2: Bruce Banner comes face to face with the Hulk's oldest enemy - General Ross himself!
description.5: Captain America must battle Hydra in order to prevent them from releasing a computer virus on a US Navy fleet. In the process, he loses one of his greatest assets- his shield!
description.6: While aboard a flight to Alaska, Scott and Jean are attacked by agents of A.I.M.!
description.11: Reed, Sue and Franklin Richards are attacked by a deadly menace - that only Susan can see!
description.12: TWO brides for Ghost Rider, Noble Kale? Read this issue to find out why it's actually a wedding from Hell!
description.13: Spider-Man faces his biggest dilemma yet…finding the perfect presents for his friends and family! With a special appearance by…Hydro-Man!
description.15: The Black Widow spins a new web of intrigue in her Journey Into Mystery debut!
description.17: Carnage has abandoned Cletus Kasady...and bonded with the Silver Surfer! What chance does Spidey have against the seemingly unstoppable Carnage Cosmic?
description.18: Cable is surrounded! The Hellfire Club may pose the biggest threat to this grim and gunned mutant!
description.20: The truth of what happened at Camp Verde has left Warpath dead! Not all hope is lost for the fallen mutant! Moonstar receives a visit from an old friend who can help…by sending the team on a rescue mission to hell!
description.23: It's business as usual for dashing multi-millionaire Tony Stark and his armored alter ego, Iron Man, now that he's returned to the Marvel Universe- or is it? Tony must decide whether to wrest control of the Stark/Fujikawa Corporation from his business "partners" or seek to increase his already vast fortune in other ways. He'd better make up his mind quickly, before a mysterious third party hires the Deathsquad to make it up for him!
description.24: The last member of the'Crimson Guard,'Kir Kanos, has found some possible allies with a band of'Rebels, but can they trust a former servant of the evil'Emperor? This issue also details an amazing untold encounter with'Darth Vader'and'Emperor'Palpatine! Plus, not one, but two groups of'Imperials'are after Kanos, with their own agendas!
description.25: Collects Boba Fett: Bounty on Bar-Kooda, Boba Fett: When the Fat Lady Swings, Boba Fett: Murder Most Foul.  Boba Fett pursues an intergalactic magician who may hold the key to the Hutt's future. The fact that the magician has died only poses a slight problem for the bounty hunter...not even the dead can escape Boba Fett!
description.26: HIDDEN HEARTS- The Fantastic Four face off against Mole Man and his tremor Trigger!
description.31: A 50th issue special! Cable, Jean Grey, and Cyclops have a family reunion unlike any you’ve ever seen!
description.32: Wedge Antilles has some news that his fellow Rogues are not going to like. If they were hesitant to fly against Baron Fel, the Empire's greatest fighter ace, how are they going to feel if they have to fly with him?
description.34: Noah had an ark and so does Doom. Doctor Doom ushers all of Earth' super heroes back to planet Earth. This is the Return!
description.36: Elektra suffers a personal loss at the hands of Kuroyama. Wolverine provides back-up in the assassin's revenge mission against The Hand.
description.37: Carnage is on the rampage, and only Spider-Man stands in his way! Luckily, Peter Parker doesn't stand alone, thanks to the arrival of the Silver Surfer! But what secret history does the Surfer have with the symbiote?
description.39: Witness the untold story of Bruce Banner's private war - in the depths of his own mind!
description.42: Steve Rogers finds himself on the streets of Tokyo with no memory of where he has been for the last year. Before he can get his bearings, Captain America is called into action to stop a group of terrorists who are protesting the Americanization of Japanese culture.
description.43: Cecilia Reyes tries to return to her life as a "normal" human. But an encounter with Pyro may force her to reconsider.
description.48: Marvel's First Family is back! The Fantastic Four find themselves in Paris, where investigating an ancient force in a historic underground passage brings them face to face with a new threat- The Ruined! Are the FF ready to leap back into action?
description.51: Doctor Strange and Spider-Man continue their dimensional traveling after defeating Buel.
description.61: Deng Ling-Xiao is fearless as the White Tiger...even as his HQ burns around him, threatening to engulf him in flames!
description.66: When Warpath and Siryn are pulled over by corrupt cops, it starts them down the path to finally finding the answers about what really happened to Warpath's tribe. Those answers might come at too high of a cost for one member of X-Force.
description.69: And you thought LAST issue was crazy? TWO Hulks battle it out underwater! Spider-Man discovers his fellow heroes, once thought to be dead, are ALIVE!
description.70: When Imperials, disguised as security personnel, break into the palace and try to snatch Jacen and Jaina Solo, they're forced to deal with the likes of Mara and Han; but who's side is Mara really on? T
description.71: The Battle Begins! Iron Man and Hulk! Doctor Strange and Loki! Meanwhile, the clock is ticking for Franklin Richards' decision on which Earth to save.
description.73: The Hellfire Club catches up to Cable! While trying to pin down the motives of Inner Circle members Sebastian Shaw and Donald Pierce, our time-tossed hero runs afoul of Paladin!
description.80: Kir Kanos'is the last surviving member of the elite'Crimson Guard. He's on the run, and the'Empire'will stop at nothing to destroy him. Featuring flashback appearances detailing the unknown pasts of'Emperor'Palpatine and'Darth Vader.
description.81: Shot down from the bloody skies of Brentaal, Baron Soontir Fel has been captured by the Rebel Alliance. But from the shadowed recesses of a Rebel interrogation chamber, The Empire's greatest fighter ace tells a story of the deception and corruption beneath the Empire's orderly surface... and sets the stage for his own defection to the Alliance!
description.82: Facing defeat at the hands of Ghaur and his men, the Heroes for Hire are helped out by Ant-Man who has secretly been serving the team!
description.83: Elektra and Matt are on their way to reconciliation, when an old samurai begging for an honor killing places the couple at a moral impasse.
description.85: A stand-alone adventure for the galaxy's most feared bounty hunter! Get a glimpse into the past of Boba Fett- from his origin as a clone to the sole protector of Jango Fett's legacy!
description.86: All of Earth's heroes remain trapped on a Counter-Earth! Franklin Richards has the power of choice. Two worlds exist. He must build a life on one of these worlds, while the other will be destroyed. This series is a direct sequel to the Onslaught event!
description.87: Doctor Strange joins the fight and leads Spider-Man from one dimensional rift to another in order to confront Buel.
description.90: Absorbing Man and Titania disguise themselves as "Lightening Bolt" and "Thundergirl" to find Spider-Man. Spider-man encounters Daredevil and battles the foes only to save Titania after a helicopter crash and helps Absorbing Man surrender. Guest Starring, The Man with No Fear: Daredevil
description.91: Shang-Chi, Master of Kung Fu vs. The Wild Tiger! Even with steel claws, will this opponent stand a chance?
description.92: Working as bodyguards should be easy money for the mutants of X-Force, but their employer may have kept some key details from the team. Meanwhile, Siryn and Warpath continue to search for answers!
description.97: Rumble in the sewers! The Hulk has made it to New York, and all he wants to do is lay low and be left alone. But the Abomination has other plans! Watch the latest chapter in this monstrous rivalry unfold, as only one monster will walk away!

0.text: Elektra's off to Japan! While there, the assassin meets two of Wolverine's oldest friends, Yukio and young Amiko. Featuring the Silver Samurai!

1.text: To save the world from unknown assassins, a new Champion must rise! And Excalibur plans to find out who deserves that role by holding a tournament! But will it be in time?

3.text: An aspect of Green Goblin haunts Spider-Man in a ghoulish fray.

7.text: Wolverine explains to Marrow how things run at the Xavier Institute, but she shows little respect for his authority, and they challenge each other to a fight in the empty danger room!

8.text: Doctor Angst sets his sights on Spider-Man, and the wall-crawler is tested to his physical and psychological limits!

9.text: Mephisto is dead. The Silver Surfer is dead. On this journey to the underworld, there is no hope. But back on Earth, Scrier, Agatha Harkness and Alicia Masters attempt to reanimate the Surfer.

10.text: Zemo unveils his plan for world domination -- but which of the Thunderbolts will side with him?

14.text: The Plunderer teams up with perhaps the most dangerous Marvel villain…Ka-Zar takes on a mission far from his wheelhouse when he does battle with Thanos!

16.text: The ever-restless Quicksilver can’t seem to keep calm while visiting New Attilan, home world of the Inhumans. What is the source of Quicksilver’s restlessness? Guest-starring the Inhuman Royal Family and the villainy of Maximus the Mad!

18.text: Cable is surrounded! The Hellfire Club may pose the biggest threat to this grim and gunned mutant!

19.text: Kitty Pryde grows up quickly when she must defeat a demonic spirit and battle Ogun for the last time!

22.text: The first appearance of May "Mayday" Parker!

26.text: HIDDEN HEARTS- The Fantastic Four face off against Mole Man and his tremor Trigger!

28.text: While Matt recovers from his wounds, Karen blows off steam, (and spite), with a shopping spree on Matt’s credit card. Daredevil meets up with Black Widow to discuss the kiss they shared. Is DD’s love with Karen in jeopardy? Has he at long last been caught in Widow’s web?

31.text: A 50th issue special! Cable, Jean Grey, and Cyclops have a family reunion unlike any you’ve ever seen!

33.text: The X-Men get a medieval makeover! In this special 0.5 issue, Mesmero creates an elaborate illusion that turns the X-Universe on its head! Nightcrawler, a swashbuckling knight! Shadowcat, an elven maiden!

35.text: Jim Hammond summons the aid of the Thunderbolts against the Deviant attack in New York.

36.text: Elektra suffers a personal loss at the hands of Kuroyama. Wolverine provides back-up in the assassin's revenge mission against The Hand.

38.text: Colossus, Nightcrawler and Kitty Pryde are made to pay for their past as members of the X-Men!

44.text: At the Xavier Institute, the X-Men begin a relatively quiet day!

46.text: Scrier, a cosmic being who’s ‘the architect of the Earth’, is the only one that can save Surfer from a soul-ravaging virus.

47.text: The Thunderbolts are revealed to the world as the Masters of Evil!

49.text: Deadpool teams up with a Japanese-speaking, dwarfed clone of himself named Widdle Wade!

50.text: Three stories starring Deadpool! The Merc with a Mouth goes to the aquarium with Blind Al, learns to be a Good Samaritan with Captain America, and crashes a birthday party (literally) with Blarney the dinosaur!

52.text: Spider-Man teams up with Sorcerer Supreme Doctor Strange to defeat Baron Mordo.

53.text: The mighty powerful Thanos faces Ka-Zar!

54.text: In-depth profiles of the X-Men from Professor Xavier's trademark intelligence machine!

55.text: Seer, a minion of Doctor Doom, has a prophecy of an all-powerful being known as Onslaught -- no surprise that megalomaniacal Doom seeks to harness its power!

56.text: Thor and the Silver Surfer travel into the past to find out what led to Asgard’s demise!

57.text: J. Jonah Jameson is investigating Bastion. Agent Smith hires Venom to scare JJJ and keep him and the newspaper away from a certain story.

58.text: Eddie is being hunted by everyone, Spider-Man included. Brock must make one final decision that will forever change the fate of the Lethal Protector.

59.text: The Thing takes center stage in an alternate universe tale featuring the Frightful Four!

60.text: The Champions and X-Force team-up to deal with a threat out of Greek myths!

62.text: A battle 55 years in the making… Against the power of Baron Zemo!

63.text: Quicksilver continues to duel with Arkon of Polemachus, when Crystal of the Inhumans bursts back on the scene! After being transported to one of Franklin Richards’ dimensions, Crystal returns to Earth alongside the Fantastic Four and Avengers. Pietro reunites with the woman he loves.

64.text: Kitty’s former teacher is on the attack for her soul! Meanwhile, Rigby tries to win Kitty’s heart and Lockheed is back with the living.

65.text: Karma possesses every member of the old (and present) New Mutants!

73.text: The Hellfire Club catches up to Cable! While trying to pin down the motives of Inner Circle members Sebastian Shaw and Donald Pierce, our time-tossed hero runs afoul of Paladin!

76.text: Held captive by the Russians, Daredevil and Black Widow set aside their differences and align themselves to escape! Once freed from their bonds, the heroes try to take down the Russian Mafia. Daredevil recruits two Soviet allies.

82.text: Facing defeat at the hands of Ghaur and his men, the Heroes for Hire are helped out by Ant-Man who has secretly been serving the team!

83.text: Elektra and Matt are on their way to reconciliation, when an old samurai begging for an honor killing places the couple at a moral impasse.

84.text: Quicksilver and his Knights of Wundagore set up camp along the Hudson River. But no sooner are they settled into their castle, when the team faces a threat from Thundra, time-traveling warrior woman! But what has drawn Thundra to the present?

88.text: What happens when a city becomes the SAVAGE LAND?!

89.text: The Overreach Committee has it out for Venom. Spider-Man shows up for the fight on backup, but Venom slips past his web-shooters once more!

93.text: They are lifelong enemies, yet are bonded by a shadowy past under the employ of Weapon X. See the blood feud between Wolverine and Sabretooth boil over, as we explore their history in this savage, battle royale issue!

96.text: Wolfsbane, Colossus, and Banshee will put it all on the line for a member of Excalibur!
